messages.content: Muns are nigh-immortal plasma-based alien beings who exist outside the multiverse, living in a place called the void
When they are created/born they are assigned their humans (although most are unaware of this) and develop their personality traits and appearances
When they’re of age, they’re sent down into the multiverse to either set worlds on the right path (saviors) or destroy them to create energy for the void (reapers)
These are basically jobs, they get paid and everything
However, normally they don’t remember anything when they go down into the multiverse and inhabit their human’s body
@Iris @g o d
O I C
Not all Muns are 1:1 with their human selves, some are younger
All Muns use they/them, on top of their usual gendered pronouns
Muns are around twice as tall as their human counterparts. They all have tails that are unique to them, and a special ability that is like their stand/hamon.
Bit of mun slang: the “main narrative” refers to the most common events that happen in each timeline
Muns have a very high number of LGBTs among their ranks

Polyamory, while somewhat uncommon, is acceptable
